{
  "dialogueGraphs": [
    {
      "id": "DG_OPERATIONAL_VERIFICATION_BINDER",
      "sceneId": "SCN-038",
      "startNodeId": "N_START",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "N_START",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The procedure binder is open to a laminated divider: OPERATIONAL STATUS VERIFICATION \u2014 DO NOT INITIATE UNLESS READY TO COMPLETE. A sticky note covers part of the header: \u201cReady means paper-ready, not emotionally ready.\u201d",
          "next": "N_PREREQS"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PREREQS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Four prerequisites are stamped in green ink: Training Gate Cleared. LOTO Tagged. Vent Damper Open. There is no stamp for \u201cThis is a good idea.\u201d",
          "next": "N_PLAYER_MURMUR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PLAYER_MURMUR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Operational verification.",
          "next": "N_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LOOK",
              "text": "Look: Review the checklist summary.",
              "next": "N_LOOK_SUMMARY_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "TALK",
              "text": "Talk: Call the assurance line.",
              "next": "N_TALK_PHONE_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE",
              "text": "Use: Initiate Operational Status Verification.",
              "next": "N_INITIATE_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "Leave: Close the binder.",
              "next": "N_CLOSE_1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_SUMMARY_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The summary page is written in a font that assumes it will be photocopied until the end of time.",
          "next": "N_LOOK_SUMMARY_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_SUMMARY_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Step headings: Confirm control authority. Confirm load characteristics. Execute reflectivity test if indicated. Someone has underlined \u201cif indicated\u201d hard enough to crease the paper.",
          "next": "N_LOOK_PLAYER_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_PLAYER_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Reflectivity test.",
          "next": "N_LOOK_FOOTNOTE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_FOOTNOTE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A footnote reads: \u201cReflectivity is a behavioral descriptor and does not imply optical compliance.\u201d The ink looks resentful.",
          "next": "N_MENU_POST_LOOK"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_MENU_POST_LOOK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE",
              "text": "Use: Initiate Operational Status Verification.",
              "next": "N_INITIATE_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "TALK",
              "text": "Talk: Call the assurance line.",
              "next": "N_TALK_PHONE_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_BACK",
              "text": "Ask: Put the summary back and return to the divider.",
              "next": "N_MENU"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "Leave: Close the binder.",
              "next": "N_CLOSE_1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TALK_PHONE_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The console\u2019s desk phone has an extension label: EAC ASSURANCE \u2014 DOCUMENTATION SUPPORT ONLY. The handset cord is too short, as if designed to discourage pacing.",
          "next": "N_TALK_PLAYER_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TALK_PLAYER_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Assurance line.",
          "next": "N_LIAISON_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LIAISON_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "EAC_LIAISON",
          "text": "Hi\u2014yes. This is Assurance. (pause) Just to be crisp: we don\u2019t authorize operations. (pause) We observe the paperwork around operations.",
          "next": "N_LIAISON_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LIAISON_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "EAC_LIAISON",
          "text": "And before you say \u201cstart\u201d (pause) I need to know what you mean (pause) by \u201cstart.\u201d (pause) \u201cStart\u201d here is a traceable state. (pause) It is not a facility change. (pause) Legally that matters. (pause) Also what is this comparable to. (pause) Turbine cold start. (pause) Boiler recommission. (pause) Substation return to service. (pause) Pick one (pause) so the file has a spine.",
          "next": "N_TALK_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TALK_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "ASK_WHY",
              "text": "Ask: Why do you need \u201ccomparable\u201d?",
              "next": "N_ASK_COMP_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_OBJ",
              "text": "Ask: Any objection to me initiating?",
              "next": "N_ASK_OBJ_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "PERSUADE_TIGHT",
              "text": "Persuade: Log it as \u201csubstation return-to-service\u201d and keep it tight.",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "bureaucracy",
                  "dc": 12
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N_PERSUADE_PASS",
              "onFailNext": "N_PERSUADE_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE",
              "text": "Use: Initiate Operational Status Verification.",
              "next": "N_INITIATE_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "Leave: Hang up.",
              "next": "N_HANGUP_1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_COMP_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Why comparable.",
          "next": "N_ASK_COMP_LIAISON"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_COMP_LIAISON",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "EAC_LIAISON",
          "text": "Auditors don\u2019t audit \u201cunique.\u201d (pause) They audit categories. (pause) If we can\u2019t categorize it (pause) every question becomes original research. (pause) No one here is funded for that. (pause) Not you. (pause) Not me. (pause) Definitely not the municipality. (pause) So we pick the least-wrong cousin (pause) and document deviations. (pause) It\u2019s a kindness. (pause) It\u2019s also self-preservation.",
          "next": "N_ASK_COMP_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_COMP_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE",
              "text": "Use: Initiate Operational Status Verification.",
              "next": "N_INITIATE_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_COUSIN",
              "text": "Ask: So what\u2019s your least-wrong cousin?",
              "next": "N_COUSIN_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "Leave: Hang up.",
              "next": "N_HANGUP_1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COUSIN_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Least-wrong cousin.",
          "next": "N_COUSIN_LIAISON"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COUSIN_LIAISON",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "EAC_LIAISON",
          "text": "Substation return-to-service with unusual optical characteristics. (pause) I\u2019m not saying it\u2019s optical. (pause) I\u2019m saying the template exists. (pause) Templates survive discovery. (pause) Don\u2019t say \u201chazard\u201d on open comms. (pause) Say \u201ccharacteristic.\u201d",
          "next": "N_COUSIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COUSIN_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE",
              "text": "Use: Initiate Operational Status Verification.",
              "next": "N_INITIATE_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_BACK",
              "text": "Ask: Go back to the main options.",
              "next": "N_TALK_MENU"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "Leave: Hang up.",
              "next": "N_HANGUP_1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_OBJ_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Any objection.",
          "next": "N_ASK_OBJ_LIAISON"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_OBJ_LIAISON",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "EAC_LIAISON",
          "text": "I can\u2019t object. (pause) I can only note. (pause) I will note: initiation creates an obligation. (pause) Complete it\u2014or formally suspend, with justification. (pause) That\u2019s not a threat. (pause) It\u2019s how paperwork breeds. (pause) You\u2019re about to feed it.",
          "next": "N_ASK_OBJ_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_OBJ_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE",
              "text": "Use: Initiate Operational Status Verification.",
              "next": "N_INITIATE_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_BACK",
              "text": "Ask: Go back to the main options.",
              "next": "N_TALK_MENU"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "Leave: Hang up.",
              "next": "N_HANGUP_1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PERSUADE_PASS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "EAC_LIAISON",
          "text": "Accepted. (pause) \u201cSubstation return-to-service\u201d gives the file a spine. (pause) Keep your language categorical and boring. (pause) Boring survives.",
          "next": "N_PERSUADE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PERSUADE_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "EAC_LIAISON",
          "text": "I can\u2019t sign off on \u201ctight.\u201d (pause) Pick the comparable out loud. (pause) Then document deviations. (pause) We do clarity not bravery.",
          "next": "N_PERSUADE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PERSUADE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE",
              "text": "Use: Initiate Operational Status Verification.",
              "next": "N_INITIATE_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_BACK",
              "text": "Ask: Return to the binder.",
              "next": "N_MENU"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "Leave: Hang up.",
              "next": "N_HANGUP_1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_HANGUP_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The line clicks off cleanly, as if relieved not to be involved.",
          "next": "N_HANGUP_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_HANGUP_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The binder remains open, patient and procedural.",
          "next": "N_MENU_AFTER_HANGUP"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_MENU_AFTER_HANGUP",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE",
              "text": "Use: Initiate Operational Status Verification.",
              "next": "N_INITIATE_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK",
              "text": "Look: Review the checklist summary.",
              "next": "N_LOOK_SUMMARY_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_BACK",
              "text": "Ask: Return to the divider menu.",
              "next": "N_MENU"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "Leave: Close the binder.",
              "next": "N_CLOSE_1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_INITIATE_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The initiation page is a single sheet on heavier paper, like it expects to be presented in a hearing.",
          "next": "N_INITIATE_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_INITIATE_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Fields: Initiator Name. Badge. Time (24h). Scope. A boxed note reads: \u201cInitiation indicates readiness to document outcomes. It does not indicate predicted safety.\u201d The box is outlined twice.",
          "next": "N_INITIATE_PLAYER_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_INITIATE_PLAYER_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Name. Time. Scope.",
          "next": "N_CONFIRM_INITIATION"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CONFIRM_INITIATION",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_CONFIRM",
              "text": "Use: Sign/initial and enter time.",
              "next": "N_ACTIVATE_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_ABORT",
              "text": "Leave: Not yet.",
              "next": "N_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACTIVATE_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You enter your details and initial the margin. The pen drags, then bites, like the paper is laminated with reluctance.",
          "next": "N_ACTIVATE_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACTIVATE_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A perforated strip tears free automatically from the bottom edge: VERIFICATION ACTIVE \u2014 RETAIN ON PERSON.",
          "next": "N_ACTIVATE_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACTIVATE_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "In the printer tray, the feed motor wakes up. The first page doesn\u2019t print yet. It just decides it will.",
          "next": "N_ACTIVATE_4"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACTIVATE_4",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A new checkbox appears at the top of the active checklist: Reflectivity Test \u2014 REQUIRED.",
          "next": "N_END_VERIFICATION"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_END_VERIFICATION",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "begin_operational_verification",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "ops.operationalVerificationStarted",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "objectives.performReflectivityTest",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CLOSE_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You close the binder. The rings clack shut like a small verdict.",
          "next": "N_CLOSE_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CLOSE_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Nothing changes, which is its own kind of decision.",
          "next": "N_END_NOCHANGE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_END_NOCHANGE",
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
